The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | US replaces top Afghan commander
                                                                                                               US replaces top Afghan commander
                            
	Washington, May 11 (Reuters): US defence secretary Robert Gates has decided to replace the top American and Nato commander in Afghanistan, General David McKiernan, less than a year after he took over the war effort there, officials said today.        
	Speaking on condition of anonymity, they said McKiernan will be replaced by Army Lieutenant General Stanley McChrystal, who is currently director of the US militarys Joint Staff. McChrystal is a former commander of special operations forces attuned to the style of counter-insurgency combat that the Obama administration has adopted as its strategy to thwart the Taliban and other militant groups.        
	Officials declined to say why Gates decided to replace McKiernan. But the change comes as top US officials, including General David Petraeus who overseas military strategy for the region, implements Obamas new strategic plan for Afghanistan .                                                                                                                                                                              
